member.summary:
A small status or count badge. A leaf component (no separate primitive needed);
styling is CSS-variable driven (see dx-display.css). Use  for a
bare status dot, otherwise the content (or ) is shown.

A labelled checkbox built on a native <input type="checkbox"> for
free accessibility and keyboard handling, with a styled box. Two-way bind via
@bind-Value. Styling is CSS-variable driven (see dx-layout.css).

A persistent, collapsible side panel that pushes content rather than overlaying
it — the non-modal counterpart to . No backdrop, no focus
trap, no scroll lock: the panel simply collapses its width (a CSS transition)
and the main content reflows. Use it for app sidebars and navigation rails;
use  when you need a modal overlay. Two-way bind via
@bind-Open. Styling is token-driven (see dx-structure.css).
